Two nations separated by a common language an ancient game played in white and a form of rounders played in pyjamas.
"To go in" and its fuller version "to go in to bat" date from, at the latest, the early 18th century - a century before baseball. We have two parallel idioms, one with leather and willow, the other with cheerleaders, but with similar meanings.
